transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'd like to reorder my prescription, please. My Cialis.

Speaker 1: Okay, sir. Can I have your first and last name, please?

Speaker 2: Richard.

Speaker 1: Sikora, S-Y-K-O-R-A.

Speaker 2: Okay, Mr. Sikora. It looks like you were getting 50 pills at a time. Did you want to do that same order again today?

Speaker 1: Yes, please.

Speaker 2: Okay, perfect.

Speaker 1: And you're still there at PO Box 622, Forest Hill, California. That's correct?

Speaker 2: I have a question if I can, please.

Speaker 1: Of course.

Speaker 2: Do you have those little red pills made by Viagra, I think?

Speaker 1: We do not, unfortunately.

Speaker 2: We are... they aren't, I don't believe those are FDA approved, and we don't sell those as of now. Maybe in the future.

Speaker 1: But I couldn't say.

Speaker 2: Okay. Well, thank you very much. Just thought I'd ask.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: And I have your Visa here, Richard, that ends in 6851. Is that the card you wanted to use today?

Speaker 1: 6851? No, no, that's not one.

Speaker 2: Okay, I can take a new card number whenever you're ready.

Speaker 1: Yes, I'm ready.

Speaker 2: We got scammed and so I got all new cards.

Speaker 1: Anyway, I believe it. It's aâ€”

Speaker 2: Visa?

Speaker 1: Visa, yeah.

Speaker 2: 4 4 0 0.

Speaker 1: 6 6 3 5.

Speaker 2: 8 0 2 0.

Speaker 1: 6 6 6 5.

Speaker 2: 0 6.

Speaker 1: 3 0. And then the CVV code?

Speaker 2: 1 1 3.

Speaker 1: Just a second. I'm going to process this order for you now. You said 1 1 3?

Speaker 2: Yes, that's correct.

Speaker 1: All righty, so you're all set, Richard. Your order's been placed. You're going to see that process, ship out, and arrive in the next few days, okay?

Speaker 2: How many days approximately?

Speaker 1: If you have that, three to five, I would say.

Speaker 2: By Friday at the absolute latest?

Speaker 1: Monday.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right. Very good. Thank you, sir.

Speaker 2: No problem. Thank you.

Speaker 1: You betcha. Bye now.
